The information we collect through our Services may include:

your contact information (name, postal or email address, phone number, etc.);
your demographic information;
information about the device you use to connect or interact with our Services, including geo-location;
details about your online activity, use and interaction with our Services;
your vehicle information;
your financial information (income, assets, employment information, etc.);
your shopping and other personal preferences; and
social media details and any other information you choose to share on those platforms.

How We Use Your Information
We may use the information we collect to:

provide the Services;
communicate with you;
provide and promote our products and Services;
advertise and market to you;
operate our business;
analyze the use of our products and Services;
facilitate FordDirect employee recruitment; and
comply with applicable laws, rules and our policies.

Information Sharing
We may share the information we collect:

within our enterprise;
with our suppliers;
with our affiliates, Dealers, Dealer Associations, and business customers;
with our marketing partners;
with third parties;
as we otherwise may notify you; and
if FordDirect or its assets are acquired.

